# NSSAAF Implementation Methodology

## Golden Rule: Always Start with GSD State

When implementing any NSSAAF code, follow this reading order:

```
1. ALWAYS read: .planning/STATE.md           ← Start here (50 lines)
2. ALWAYS read: .planning/PROJECT.md         ← Project context
3. THEN read:   docs/quickref.md             ← 5G domain quick reference
4. THEN read:   .planning/REQUIREMENTS.md    ← Active requirements
5. THEN read:   docs/roadmap/PHASE_*.md       ← Relevant phase plan
6. THEN read:   docs/design/XX_*.md          ← Relevant design doc
7. THEN write code
```

For the current phase (Phase 4), also read:
```
8. .planning/phases/04-NFIntegration_Observability/04-CONTEXT.md
   ← Captured implementation decisions
```

## Context Budget

NSSAAF has 20 design docs (~11,000 lines). Load no more than **200 lines at a time.**

| What you need | Read this | Lines |
|---|---|---|
| Current position | `.planning/STATE.md` | 50 |
| Project overview | `.planning/PROJECT.md` | 120 |
| Active requirements | `.planning/REQUIREMENTS.md` | 150 |
| Phase overview | `docs/roadmap/PHASE_*.md` | 150 |
| Design detail | `docs/design/02_nssaa_api.md` | 574 |
| Quick reference | `docs/roadmap/module_index.md` | 50 |

When orchestrating subagents, read only frontmatter/summaries for phases outside the current active work. See `references/universal-anti-patterns.md` for full context budget rules.

